# PLAN — EVA Machine Trust Index (47-eva-mti)

**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** 2026-02-23 16:33 ET  
**Owner:** AICOE

> This file documents the design and implementation phases for the EVA Machine Trust Index (MTI) and Trust Service.  
> The MTI specification was developed in `19-ai-gov` and separated into this project on Feb 23, 2026.  
> Implementing teams read the specs here and author their own backlogs.

---

## Design Phases (Inherited from 19-ai-gov)

The following specification work was completed in 19-ai-gov before the split. It is fully inherited by this project.

### Phase 1 — MTI Concept and Subscore Definitions (Complete)

**M-01 · MTI Concept and Rationale**  
Define the Machine Trust Index as a dynamic, evidence-based, contextual trust score for EVA actors. Establish that trust is computed (not assumed) across 6 independent dimensions.  
Basis: NuEnergy.ai / DGC-CGN Machine Trust Index White Paper (2020).  
→ `EVA-Machine-trust-Index.md` (reference copy in 19-ai-gov)  
**Status: Complete (inherited)**

**M-02 · 6 Subscore Definitions**  
Define ITI, BTI, CTI, ETI, STI, ARI — each with data sources, inputs, and example values.

| Subscore | Full Name | Core Measurement |
|---|---|---|
| ITI | Identity Trust Index | Auth strength, MFA, ToU, role maturity |
| BTI | Behaviour Trust Index | Violations, anomalies, denial patterns |
| CTI | Compliance Trust Index | % controls + obligations satisfied |
| ETI | Evidence Trust Index | Pack completeness, SHA-256 validation |
| STI | Security Trust Index | Prompt injection, exfil, anomaly signals |
| ARI | Agent Reliability Index | Hallucination rate, grounding, red team |

→ `eva-mti-scope.md` (reference copy in 19-ai-gov)  
**Status: Complete (inherited)**

---

### Phase 2 — Computation Specification (Complete)

**M-03 · Computation Formulas and Weights**  
Define the full computation model: per-subscore input → score formula, actor-type weight tables (HUMAN vs AGENT vs SERVICE vs SYSTEM), composite formula, normalization, decay model, missing signal penalty, success boost cap.  
→ `eva-mti-compute-specs.md` (reference copy in 19-ai-gov)  
**Status: Complete (inherited) — YAML has HTML entity issue (reference only)**

**M-04 · Trust Bands and Allowed-Actions Matrix**  
Define the 5 trust bands (UNTRUSTED / LOW / GUARDED / TRUSTED / HIGH TRUST) and map each band to allowed action categories across 9 dimensions.  
→ `eva-mti-actions-matrix.md` (reference copy in 19-ai-gov)  
**Status: Complete (inherited)**

---

### Phase 3 — Trust Service API Contract (Complete)

**M-05 · OpenAPI 3.0 Trust Service Contract**  
Full OpenAPI 3.0 spec for the Trust Service surface:

| Endpoint | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `POST /trust/evaluateTrust` | Compute all 6 subscores + Composite MTI |
| `GET /trust/getActorTrust/{actorId}` | Retrieve current and historical MTI scores |
| `POST /trust/getDecision` | Full governance decision (calls policy layer) |
| `POST /trust/signal` | Ingest trust signal event, trigger async MTI recompute |

→ `eva-mti-trust-service-api.md` (reference copy in 19-ai-gov)  
**Status: Complete (inherited) — YAML has HTML entity issue (reference only)**

---

### Phase 4 — Cosmos Container Schema (Complete)

**M-06 · `actor_trust_scores` Container Schema**  
Define the Cosmos container that stores per-actor MTI history: composite score, all 6 subscores, timestamp, context snapshot, computation version. Supports 30-day lookback for audit.  
→ `eva-api-n-cosmos-container.md` §actor_trust_scores (reference copy in 19-ai-gov)  
**Status: Complete (inherited)**

---

## Open Work — Implementation

The design is complete. Implementing teams should review the specs and make their own decisions on the following.

### Phase 5 — Trust Service Implementation (Not Started)

**M-07 · Trust Service Runtime**  
Build and deploy the Trust Service API. Candidate host: `29-foundry`.

Implementation requirements from specs:
- Stateless HTTP service — compute subscores per request, store result per actor
- Signal ingestion endpoint (`/signal`) triggers async Cosmos write + recompute queue
- Governance catalog read: CTI and ETI inputs come from `governance_evaluations` and `evidence_artifacts`
- Entra ID bearer auth on all endpoints
- p95 latency: `/evaluateTrust` <= 150 ms, `/getDecision` <= 200 ms

**Status: Not started**

**M-08 · Subscore Data Pipeline**  
Wire signal sources to subscore inputs:

| Subscore | Signal Source | Integration Project |
|---|---|---|
| ITI | Entra ID token claims, RBAC role assignments | 28-rbac |
| BTI | audit_events, APIM denial logs | 40-eva-control-plane, 17-apim |
| CTI | governance_evaluations, obligation_instances | 19-ai-gov runtime |
| ETI | evidence_artifacts validation events | 40-eva-control-plane |
| STI | APIM threat headers, App Insights anomaly | 17-apim, 29-foundry |
| ARI | EVA Brain evaluation telemetry, red team results | 33-eva-brain-v2, 36-red-teaming |

**Status: Not started**

**M-09 · YAML Spec Remediation**  
Strip `&nbsp;` HTML entities from `eva-mti-compute-specs.md` and `eva-mti-trust-service-api.md` to produce parse-ready YAML. Create clean copies in this project's directory.

**Status: Not started**

